      "content": "makes sense. so, looking at the two sides, which approach do you think is more legally sound? like, is it more legitimate for judges to focus on strictly following the written text and procedural rules, or is the 'living constitution' approach you mentioned earlier a more accurate way to uphold the actual spirit of the law?",
